Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["HyperIntica", "ObjectName",ExpressionUUID->"2dc2f899-702e-49a8-8fbb-5303128c50f7"],

Cell[BoxData[GridBox[{
   {Cell[TextData[{
     StyleBox["HyperIntica", "TI"],
     " \[LineSeparator]While HyperIntica is the main (analytic) integration \
routine working under the hood of the STIntegrate function, it can also be \
used as a standalone function."
    }], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"d40bbf82-5d01-41f9-9718-4001f73e4458"]}
  },
  GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Left}}},
  GridBoxItemSize->{
   "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}]], "Usage",
 CellID->1,ExpressionUUID->"37e9491a-5944-414d-958a-323bf8f79495"],

Cell["\<\
While HyperIntica is the main (analytic) integration routine working under \
the hood of the STIntegrate function, it can also be used as a standalone \
function. It evaluates iterated integrals \[Integral]_0^\[Infinity] \
\[Ellipsis] \[Integral]_0^\[Infinity] f\\, dx_1 \[Ellipsis] dx_n in  for \
expressions built from hyperlogarithms, polylogarithms, logarithms, and \
rational functions, returning results in terms of multi-zeta values and \
hyperlogarithms in the original integrand f parameters (if any). The syntax \
is: (see example below)\
\>", "Notes",ExpressionUUID->"d6ef7bde-be82-4739-b538-4d3c17140093"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"HyperIntica", "[", 
  RowBox[{"integrand", ",", " ", "variables", ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Monitor\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "False"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",Exp\
ressionUUID->"879db629-144f-410c-bad2-d15475ae4dbd"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Details", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6565942c-9ed8-4c27-b7dc-49fae2406b0d"],

Cell["Required arguments", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"7f4bad5e-8a29-4830-a679-19d5aff557a4"],

Cell["\<\
The argument integrand accepts either a symbolic expression involving Hlog, \
Mpl, PolyLog, logarithms and/or rational functions. The argument \
variables\\,= {x_1, ..., x_n} is the ordered list of integration variables, \
each x_i integrated, left to right, from 0 to \[Infinity] by default.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4630aa99-7a7c-410a-a7a1-0fd1e9895cb9"],

Cell["Optional arguments", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"5f8982e6-5e3d-465c-8150-b5b37324047b"],

Cell["\<\
Integration bounds other than [0,\[Infinity]) can be specified in Mathematica \
Integrate-style syntax: HyperIntica[f, {x, 0, 1}, {y, 0, \[Infinity]}], where \
the allowed bounds are 0, 1, and \[Infinity]. The equivalent rule-based \
syntax {x -> {0, 1}, y -> {0, \[Infinity]}} is also accepted. The option \
\"Monitor\" -> False (default) prints progress to standard output as each \
variable is processed when set to True, useful for tracking, e.g., long \
multi-variable integrations.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"04afac62-9d59-4a4e-bcc7-5caa7b868094"],

Cell["Return value", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"744abbca-e155-4a6d-a50f-46c2a49cd0e0"],

Cell["\<\
The function returns a combination of multi-zeta values, transcendental \
constants (such as log(2)), and hyperlogarithms in any remaining parameters. \
Some simple examples of usage are: (see example below) If the output of \
HyperIntica depends on zeroInfPeriod, one can try to simplify it in terms of \
multi-zeta values by apply CleanZeroInf[] to the output.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1c1bf136-a79e-43b1-b9a9-0087b8ca5813"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
   RowBox[{"Univariate", " ", "integral"}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"HyperIntica", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Log", "[", "z", "]"}], "/", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"1", " ", "-", " ", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"{", "z", "}"}], "^", "2"}]}]}], ")"}]}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", "z", "}"}]}], "]"}], " ", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Out", ":", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "3"}], " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"mzv", "[", "2", "]"}], "/", "2"}]}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", 
   "\t", "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Two", "-", 
     RowBox[{
     "variable", " ", "integral", " ", "with", " ", "finite", " ", 
      "bounds"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"HyperIntica", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"1", "/", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"1", "+", "x"}], ")"}], 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"1", "+", "y"}], ")"}]}], ")"}]}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"y", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "  ", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Out", ":", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Log", "[", "2", "]"}], "\\", "textcolor"}], 
      RowBox[{"{", "gray", "}"}], 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"{", "}"}], "^", "2"}], "}"}]}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
   "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
    "Monitor", " ", "progress", " ", "for", " ", "a", " ", "less", " ", 
     "trivial", " ", "example"}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"HyperIntica", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\\", "frac"}], 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"\\", "textcolor"}], 
        RowBox[{"{", "Maroon", "}"}], 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
             RowBox[{"{", "Log", "}"}]}], "}"}], "[", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"{", "+", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{
              RowBox[{"{", "x", "}"}], "/"}], "\\", "mathtt"}], 
            RowBox[{"{", "y", "}"}]}], "]"}], "^", "2"}], " ", "\\", 
         "textcolor"}], 
        RowBox[{"{", "Maroon", "}"}], 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
            RowBox[{"{", "Log", "}"}]}], "}"}], "[", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", "+", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}], "/"}], "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{"{", "x", "}"}]}], "]"}], " ", "\\", "textcolor"}], 
        RowBox[{"{", "Maroon", "}"}], 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{"{", "Log", "}"}]}], "}"}], "[", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
          RowBox[{"{", "y", "}"}]}], "]"}]}], "}"}], 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"(", "\n", "\t\t", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
         RowBox[{"{", "x", "}"}], " ", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", "+", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{"{", "y", "}"}]}], ")"}], " ", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", "+", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", "x", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"{", "+", "}"}], " ", "\\", "mathtt"}], 
           RowBox[{"{", "y", "}"}]}], ")"}]}], ")"}], "}"}]}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "y"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<Monitor\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "True"}]}], "]"}], "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Out", ":", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"24", "/", "5"}], "-", 
         RowBox[{"Log", "[", "512", "]"}]}], ")"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"mzv", "[", "2", "]"}], "\\", "textcolor"}], 
       RowBox[{"{", "gray", "}"}], 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"{", "}"}], "^", "2"}], "}"}]}], "-", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"27", "/", "2"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{"mzv", "[", "2", "]"}], " ", 
       RowBox[{"mzv", "[", "3", "]"}]}], "+", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"127", " ", 
         RowBox[{"mzv", "[", "5", "]"}]}], ")"}], "/", "8"}]}]}], " ", 
    "*)"}]}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"26d06eb0-68b3-4523-88cb-\
8522d895f428"],

Cell["Linear reducibility", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"9852f917-a813-4e6b-9c32-bbbd3e11fed1"],

Cell["\<\
The order of variables (i.e., the order in which we integrate) matters a lot: \
the algorithm requires each polynomial encountered during integration to \
factor linearly the current variable. When calling HyperIntica directly, a \
wrong order can silently return an incomplete (and thus incorrect) result. \
The two global flags NoAlgebraicRootsContributions and HyperWarnZeroed \
control the response to a non-linearly-factoring polynomial:   \[Bullet]  \
NoAlgebraicRootsContributions = True (default): the non-linear factor is set \
to zero. If HyperWarnZeroed = True (default), two messages fire: \
LinearFactors::nonlinear identifies the offending polynomial and \
LinearFactors::zeroed reminds the user to verify the ordering. Setting \
HyperWarnZeroed = False suppresses both reminders. In either case the result \
is 0, which is incorrect if the ordering is not linearly reducible.  \
\[Bullet]  NoAlgebraicRootsContributions = False: HyperIntica returns Failed \
immediately upon encountering the non-linear factor, with message \
LinearFactorsE::nonlinear. This makes an incorrect ordering immediately \
visible.  Note that using NoAlgebraicRootsContributions = True is safe when \
HyperIntica is called from STIntegrate, which verifies a valid order exists \
first, but it is in general advisable to verify a chosen order is linearly \
reducible by setting $NoAlgebraicRootsContributions = False before calling \
HyperIntica directly as a standalone function.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c9ca2f05-4a6a-4e37-aaee-d6038968e90e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   RowBox[{
   "Consider", " ", "the", " ", "following", " ", "function", " ", "to", " ", 
    "be", " ", "integrated", " ", "over", " ", "x", " ", "and", " ", 
    RowBox[{"y", ":"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"f", " ", "=", " ", 
     RowBox[{"1", "/", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"1", " ", "-", " ", "x", " ", "+", " ", 
        RowBox[{"x", " ", 
         RowBox[{"y", "^", "2"}]}]}], ")"}]}]}], ";"}], "\n", "\t", "\n", 
   "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Good", " ", 
      RowBox[{"order", ":", " ", 
       RowBox[{"1", "-", "x", "+", 
        RowBox[{"x", "*", 
         RowBox[{"y", "^", "2"}], " ", "is", " ", "linear", " ", "in", " ", 
         "x"}]}]}]}], ";", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
       "after", " ", "integrating", " ", "x", " ", "the", " ", "resulting", " ",
         "letter", " ", 
        RowBox[{"y", "^", "2"}]}], "-", "1"}], " ", "=", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"y", "-", "1"}], ")"}], 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"y", "+", "1"}], ")"}], " ", "factors", " ", "linearly", " ", 
       "in", " ", "y"}]}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"HyperIntica", "[", 
    RowBox[{"f", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"y", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "   ", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Out", ":", " ", 
     RowBox[{"3", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"mzv", "[", "2", "]"}], "/", "2"}]}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", 
   "\t", "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Bad", " ", 
     RowBox[{"order", ":", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"x", "*", 
        RowBox[{"y", "^", "2"}]}], "+", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"1", "-", "x"}], ")"}], " ", "does", " ", "not", " ", 
        "factor", " ", "linearly", " ", "in", " ", "y"}]}]}]}], " ", "*)"}], 
   "\n", "\t", "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"With", " ", "NoAlgebraicRootsContributions"}], " ", "=", " ", 
      "True"}], ",", "\n", "\t ", 
     RowBox[{"HyperWarnZeroed", " ", "=", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"True", " ", 
        RowBox[{"(", "defaults", ")"}]}], ":"}]}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
   
   RowBox[{"HyperIntica", "[", 
    RowBox[{"f", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"y", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"LinearFactors", "::", "nonlinear"}], " ", "and", " ", 
     RowBox[{"LinearFactors", "::", "zeroed"}], " ", "warnings", " ", "fire", 
     "\n", "\t", 
     RowBox[{"Out", ":", " ", 
      RowBox[{"0", " ", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"incorrect", "!"}], ")"}]}]}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
   "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"With", " ", "NoAlgebraicRootsContributions"}], " ", "=", " ", 
     RowBox[{"False", ":"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"HyperIntica", "[", 
    RowBox[{"f", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"y", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"LinearFactorsE", "::", "nonlinear"}], " ", "fires", "\n", "\t", 
     
     RowBox[{"Out", ":", " ", "Failed"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", "\n", 
   "\t", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{"Cross", "-", "check"}], " ", "*)"}], "\n", "\t", 
   RowBox[{"Integrate", "[", 
    RowBox[{"f", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}], ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"y", ",", " ", "0", ",", " ", "1"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "    ", 
   RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Out", ":", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Pi", "^", "2"}], "/", "4"}]}], " ", "=", " ", 
     RowBox[{"3", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"mzv", "[", "2", "]"}], "/", "2"}]}]}], " ", 
    "*)"}]}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"04b5f215-52f1-4045-8b07-\
5b3fe4c14e18"],

Cell["Divergence checking", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"0ebae8ed-8f9d-44ae-a556-d09c2726554e"],

Cell["\<\
The global flag HyperInticaCheckDivergences controls whether HyperIntica \
computes and verifies boundary expansions at each integration step. In \
HyperIntica.wl the default is True: after finding the primitive in each \
variable, the code expands the result at z=0 and z=\[Infinity], collects all \
pole terms, and checks that they cancel. If a divergence is detected and \
HyperInticaAbortOnDivergence = True (default), the computation aborts with \
Failed. Setting HyperInticaAbortOnDivergence = False instead stores the \
divergence (if any) in the association HyperInticaDivergences and continues. \
When the flag is set to False, the boundary expansions themselves are skipped \
entirely, not just the final cancellation check, so a speedup generally comes \
from avoiding the computation of the expansions altogether. When HyperIntica \
is called from within STIntegrate, the flag is automatically set to False, \
since the tropical subtraction algorithm guarantees that every counter-term \
integrand passed to HyperIntica is locally finite. When using HyperIntica as \
a standalone function on an integral whose finiteness is not known a priori, \
the user should keep HyperInticaCheckDivergences = True and \
$HyperInticaAbortOnDivergence = True (the default in standalone mode).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"913e1ff2-8385-482e-ba5f-d0c0f22e2b6b"],

Cell["Memoization and cache management", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"d37f918c-95f3-4eb7-9a19-5cdb39bf32da"],

Cell["\<\
During integration, {HyperIntica} accumulates several internal memoization \
caches. These persist for the duration of the session, which is beneficial \
when evaluating many related integrals, and can be cleared at any time by \
calling ForgetAllMemo in the notebook where calculations are done.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5952c2f9-690c-490d-8276-bfbdc31a08b7"]
}, Open  ]],

